1
00:00:02,594 --> 00:00:04,825
(Natsuno Chinami) I got a boyfriend...

2
00:00:04,825 --> 00:00:07,231
(Ayayo Noda) I also got a boyfriend. (Hikari Umaji) Congratulations!

3
00:00:07,231 --> 00:00:10,297
(Riku) My father collapsed.

4
00:00:10,297 --> 00:00:12,561
thank you. (Shibuya) Yeah.

5
00:00:15,363 --> 00:00:19,033
(Riku) I loved it. But now...➡

6
00:00:19,033 --> 00:00:23,660
When I'm with light... I feel like disappearing...

7
00:00:23,660 --> 00:00:35,528
♬〜

8
00:00:35,528 --> 00:00:38,891
And Riku-kun, haven't you heard from me yet?

9
00:00:38,891 --> 00:00:41,627
No, I haven't done it either.

10
00:00:43,198 --> 00:00:48,528
No, that's a lie. I called twice. I didn't come out though.

11
00:00:48,528 --> 00:00:50,891
I see... Well, but➡

12
00:00:50,891 --> 00:00:54,033
My luggage is still there, so I might come back.

13
00:00:59,099 --> 00:01:01,825
We were talking about going to a hot spring.

14
00:01:01,825 --> 00:01:04,033
Riku: I'm really looking forward to that.

15
00:01:06,891 --> 00:01:08,924
I'm sure he'll come back.

16
00:01:11,561 --> 00:01:15,099
I might go abroad for fun. Shall we go together?

17
00:01:15,099 --> 00:01:17,693
Ah... you guys have boyfriends, right?

18
00:01:17,693 --> 00:01:20,594
You're busy, aren't you? Hey, just because I'm lonely➡

19
00:01:20,594 --> 00:01:24,000
Don't get into trouble with that strange man again, okay? Because it's dangerous.

20
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:26,660
Yeah…. A strange man?

21
00:01:26,660 --> 00:01:30,858
Last time, when I had a fight with Riku-kun, I was almost kidnapped by a man.

22
00:01:30,858 --> 00:01:32,891
Eh!? That's an exaggeration.

23
00:01:38,825 --> 00:01:41,297
(Murata) Mr. Noda?

24
00:01:41,297 --> 00:01:44,396
Ah... I was dazed.

25
00:01:44,396 --> 00:01:46,429
(Murata) Are you okay?

26
00:01:46,429 --> 00:01:50,462
What? (Murata) No, well... somehow.

27
00:01:57,363 --> 00:02:00,891
(Murata) The number of poems has increased.

28
00:02:00,891 --> 00:02:02,924
Thanks to you. (Murata) It’s about time➡

29
00:02:02,924 --> 00:02:06,198
I want to think about design.

30
00:02:06,198 --> 00:02:09,726
I agree.

31
00:02:09,726 --> 00:02:14,759
(Murata) But this is love...➡

32
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:18,363
It's like... everyone seems to be heartbroken.

33
00:02:30,033 --> 00:02:32,396
Ah, that was fun. (Shibuya) Hahaha.

34
00:02:32,396 --> 00:02:35,297
A great buy! (Shibuya) Hehe, I bought it.

35
00:02:35,297 --> 00:02:38,462
Yes, I bought a lot of cosmetics. Ahaha.

36
00:02:38,462 --> 00:02:41,924
Just going out on a weekday is great.

37
00:02:41,924 --> 00:02:44,264
I'm glad I took the day off. (Shibuya) Hahaha. ➡

38
00:02:44,264 --> 00:02:46,429
I'll buy you something to drink. Is there anything?

39
00:02:46,429 --> 00:02:48,627
Well, it's okay because it's there. (Shibuya) Yeah, okay. ➡

40
00:02:48,627 --> 00:02:50,660
Then get in the car and wait. Yeah.

41
00:02:54,264 --> 00:02:56,297
Hmm….

42
00:03:04,858 --> 00:03:06,891
Eh...

43
00:03:06,891 --> 00:03:26,000
♬〜

44
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:46,000
♬〜

45
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
♬〜

46
00:03:54,759 --> 00:03:56,792
(Ariga) What's wrong?

47
00:04:00,363 --> 00:04:02,396
That...

48
00:04:07,297 --> 00:04:11,132
(Ariga) What? The car ➡

49
00:04:11,132 --> 00:04:15,462
This... it's like that in the sunshade. Yeah.

50
00:04:15,462 --> 00:04:20,000
Is it cheating if there's a clip of a woman over there?

51
00:04:21,495 --> 00:04:27,198
Hmm...it's a little strange.

52
00:04:27,198 --> 00:04:29,759
The person driving the car is in the passenger seat➡

53
00:04:29,759 --> 00:04:32,066
I don't really care.

54
00:04:32,066 --> 00:04:35,726
So there's a possibility that it's an ex-girlfriend.

55
00:04:38,330 --> 00:04:40,891
That's right. Hehe.

56
00:04:40,891 --> 00:04:44,891
(Ariga) He is from the publisher? Yeah well.

57
00:04:44,891 --> 00:04:49,132
Don't you have anything at home? Traces of a woman.

58
00:04:49,132 --> 00:04:51,726
I've never been home.

59
00:04:51,726 --> 00:04:55,462
(Ariga) Huh... why?

60
00:04:55,462 --> 00:04:57,891
No, why...

61
00:05:00,363 --> 00:05:03,396
(Ariga) I think that's more suspicious.

62
00:05:18,165 --> 00:05:20,198
Ratt (door sound)

63
00:05:24,660 --> 00:05:26,693
land!

64
00:05:41,000 --> 00:06:01,000
♬〜

65
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:15,462
♬〜

66
00:06:15,462 --> 00:06:19,231
📱(Guidance) Is the number you dialed in a place where there is no signal?➡

67
00:06:19,231 --> 00:06:22,198
It won't start because the power is off.

68
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:29,528
(Inner voice) ≪I won't even get a last chance...≫

69
00:06:48,198 --> 00:06:52,000
Wait a minute~ What? This air!

70
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:55,891
Huh? Wasn't Chinami in love?

71
00:06:55,891 --> 00:06:58,693
We're in love, but...

72
00:07:13,528 --> 00:07:16,891
Rikugasa…➡

73
00:07:16,891 --> 00:07:20,099
It really came out.

74
00:07:20,099 --> 00:07:23,627
The key is left➡

75
00:07:23,627 --> 00:07:25,660
My luggage is missing...

76
00:07:27,759 --> 00:07:30,033
Have you been contacted?

77
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:33,429
do not have. That's what happened when I got home from work.

78
00:07:35,561 --> 00:07:39,165
The key was left there➡

79
00:07:39,165 --> 00:07:42,660
I don't think he'll ever come back at all.

80
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:46,759
What, no letters, emails, anything like that?

81
00:07:46,759 --> 00:07:50,033
Does that mean the key was left behind? yes.

82
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,759
What is that...

83
00:07:52,759 --> 00:07:57,726
The clothes I bought for Riku were left behind...

84
00:07:57,726 --> 00:08:01,429
You don't like me that much➡

85
00:08:01,429 --> 00:08:03,462
It's been quite a while.

86
00:08:03,462 --> 00:08:07,495
Hey, wait a minute. Huh? Isn't that strange?

87
00:08:07,495 --> 00:08:10,363
Don't be fooled by the light. Not that I'm pampering you➡

88
00:08:10,363 --> 00:08:12,396
That's not what I mean... No, but like a house➡

89
00:08:12,396 --> 00:08:14,429
You let me live there, right? Because I'm not going there.

90
00:08:14,429 --> 00:08:16,462
Because I wanted to live in the house with you.

91
00:08:16,462 --> 00:08:18,495
But I did give them a lot of money.

92
00:08:18,495 --> 00:08:20,528
I did put out a little bit, though. But that too➡

93
00:08:20,528 --> 00:08:22,561
Because I did it on my own.

94
00:08:24,528 --> 00:08:27,726
Riku-kun, you're sneaky. If you don't like it, don't like it➡

95
00:08:27,726 --> 00:08:30,957
You can just say it then. Take advantage of the light...

96
00:08:30,957 --> 00:08:33,792
That's why it's different!

97
00:08:33,792 --> 00:08:36,627
Land is...➡

98
00:08:36,627 --> 00:08:40,957
I'm trying my best to live properly on my own.

99
00:08:40,957 --> 00:08:43,495
I love Riku and want to support him.

100
00:08:45,825 --> 00:08:50,165
But I think it was a little off.

101
00:08:50,165 --> 00:08:54,231
No...actually, I knew it all along.

102
00:08:56,726 --> 00:09:00,891
But I was afraid to check.

103
00:09:00,891 --> 00:09:06,660
Even if you cheat, there's no future ahead of you.

104
00:09:06,660 --> 00:09:13,297
♬〜

105
00:09:13,297 --> 00:09:15,891
Sorry, I'm going home.

106
00:09:15,891 --> 00:09:17,924
Hey, I'm sorry...

107
00:09:17,924 --> 00:09:20,891
Ayase isn't bad.

108
00:09:20,891 --> 00:09:26,660
But... I just want to cool down. sorry.

109
00:09:26,660 --> 00:09:35,297
♬〜

110
00:09:35,297 --> 00:09:37,363
⚞Rattle rattle…(door sound)

111
00:09:40,297 --> 00:09:42,330
Bang (door sound)

112
00:09:47,627 --> 00:09:51,297
(Shibuya) Welcome back. I'm home.

113
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:01,693
(Shibuya) Ah, this plate? The one I bought the other day.

114
00:10:01,693 --> 00:10:06,330
Next time I go, I want to buy a bigger one.

115
00:10:06,330 --> 00:10:11,363
So, why don't you go to the tableware shop in Aoyama this weekend?

116
00:10:11,363 --> 00:10:16,825
Ah~...I guess it's a little difficult on the weekends.

117
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:20,396
Ah...even if it's not this week.

118
00:10:20,396 --> 00:10:24,396
I haven't had weekends off for a while...

119
00:10:26,198 --> 00:10:28,924
That's right. Yeah.

120
00:10:40,825 --> 00:10:45,066
Can I go to Mr. Shibuya's house next time?

121
00:10:46,594 --> 00:10:49,198
home?

122
00:10:49,198 --> 00:10:51,231
Yeah.

123
00:11:03,363 --> 00:11:05,396
(Shibuya) It's me...

124
00:11:08,396 --> 00:11:10,693
I'm married...

125
00:11:10,693 --> 00:11:12,726
Huh?

126
00:11:12,726 --> 00:11:16,330
(Shibuya) I've always thought I had to say it.

127
00:11:16,330 --> 00:11:26,330
♬〜

128
00:11:26,330 --> 00:11:32,330
My wife and I haven't been on good terms for a long time. ➡

129
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:38,033
However, I am not divorced for the sake of my children...

130
00:11:41,396 --> 00:11:44,462
Do you have children?

131
00:11:44,462 --> 00:11:47,495
(Shibuya) Yeah...

132
00:11:47,495 --> 00:11:49,528
How many?

133
00:11:50,891 --> 00:11:53,825
10 years old and 8 years old.

134
00:11:53,825 --> 00:11:59,495
♬〜

135
00:11:59,495 --> 00:12:01,528
(Shibuya) But I'm serious about Chinami...

136
00:12:01,528 --> 00:12:05,165
Go back. (Shibuya) Chinami….

137
00:12:05,165 --> 00:12:12,396
♬〜

138
00:12:12,396 --> 00:12:14,429
Come out.

139
00:12:15,891 --> 00:12:17,924
Then I'll come out.

140
00:12:19,726 --> 00:12:22,561
Gacha (door sound) (Shibuya) Chinami!

141
00:12:22,561 --> 00:12:24,759
Bang

142
00:12:24,759 --> 00:12:26,957
(Shibuya) Chinami! Don't follow me.

143
00:12:26,957 --> 00:12:29,000
(Shibuya) Chinami!

144
00:12:29,000 --> 00:12:37,495
♬〜

145
00:12:37,495 --> 00:12:39,528
Sorry for being silent.

146
00:12:41,528 --> 00:12:43,561
I'm sorry for making you feel like you're deceiving me.

147
00:12:48,066 --> 00:12:52,528
My wife and I are planning to divorce when our child reaches junior high school.

148
00:12:54,660 --> 00:12:58,825
My marriage has long since fallen apart...

149
00:12:58,825 --> 00:13:03,792
I can't believe that.

150
00:13:03,792 --> 00:13:07,033
I understand. I know, but...

151
00:13:10,693 --> 00:13:16,165
I really fell in love with Chinami...

152
00:13:16,165 --> 00:13:21,264
♬〜

153
00:13:21,264 --> 00:13:23,297
(Shibuya) That's why I don't want to break up.

154
00:13:23,297 --> 00:13:38,165
♬〜

155
00:13:38,165 --> 00:13:40,198
(Shibuya) I'm going home today. ➡

156
00:13:40,198 --> 00:13:42,231
I will contact you again.

157
00:13:42,231 --> 00:13:55,660
♬〜

158
00:14:16,825 --> 00:14:19,396
(Murata) Hehe, that's a big catch.

159
00:14:19,396 --> 00:14:21,429
Hehe...

160
00:14:31,561 --> 00:14:34,066
No, wait a minute... No way.

161
00:14:34,066 --> 00:14:37,495
No... Parents are coming. Yay!

162
00:14:37,495 --> 00:14:40,528
Hey….

163
00:14:40,528 --> 00:14:42,858
Hey, stop it! Don!

164
00:14:58,099 --> 00:15:01,264
It's been weird lately. ➡

165
00:15:01,264 --> 00:15:04,858
Always absentminded. Did something happen?

166
00:15:08,033 --> 00:15:10,363
Nothing special though...

167
00:15:12,264 --> 00:15:15,660
(Murata) Who do you like?

168
00:15:18,891 --> 00:15:20,924
different.

169
00:15:22,792 --> 00:15:26,165
(Murata) It will be obvious. Mr. Noda is a bad liar.

170
00:15:26,165 --> 00:15:30,660
♬〜

171
00:15:30,660 --> 00:15:34,462
It's okay. Please use me➡

172
00:15:34,462 --> 00:15:37,330
Because I said so. Even if it stays this way.

173
00:15:41,297 --> 00:15:44,627
(Murata) But somehow…➡

174
00:15:44,627 --> 00:15:48,792
I was more shocked than I expected➡

175
00:15:48,792 --> 00:15:52,825
It's sad.

176
00:15:52,825 --> 00:15:56,660
I have so much fun being with Noda-san.

177
00:15:56,660 --> 00:16:04,165
♬〜

178
00:16:04,165 --> 00:16:08,330
(Murata) I'm going home today. But it's okay.

179
00:16:08,330 --> 00:16:11,396
You'll be fine soon.

180
00:16:11,396 --> 00:16:13,429
It will be put to good use again.

181
00:16:21,660 --> 00:16:27,000
⚟Rattle rattle… rattle (door sound)

182
00:16:46,099 --> 00:16:55,759
📱(Manner mode)

183
00:16:55,759 --> 00:17:05,396
📱(Manner mode)

184
00:17:05,396 --> 00:17:07,429
Click...(sound of putting down smartphone)

185
00:17:07,429 --> 00:17:13,000
📱(Manner mode)

186
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:18,726
♬〜

187
00:17:18,726 --> 00:17:20,759
📱(Message reception/Silent mode)

188
00:17:20,759 --> 00:17:25,000
♬〜

189
00:17:31,287 --> 00:17:34,386
Did Norio buy this cake?

190
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:38,188
No, Murata bought it for me.

191
00:17:38,188 --> 00:17:41,188
But I went home without eating.

192
00:17:41,188 --> 00:17:44,749
why? Something...➡

193
00:17:44,749 --> 00:17:46,881
It started like a fight.

194
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:54,749
Well, there are many kinds of love.

195
00:17:54,749 --> 00:17:57,617
Persuasive power. Hehe.

196
00:18:03,023 --> 00:18:06,551
Who is Shibuya-san? Is everything going well?

197
00:18:12,287 --> 00:18:15,056
Can you listen without backing down?

198
00:18:15,056 --> 00:18:17,485
What? It's scary though.

199
00:18:21,452 --> 00:18:26,353
Mr. Shibuya…➡

200
00:18:26,353 --> 00:18:28,386
I was married.

201
00:18:30,122 --> 00:18:33,749
Huh... that's a lie, right?

202
00:18:33,749 --> 00:18:36,155
Eh, hey➡

203
00:18:36,155 --> 00:18:39,584
I... we broke up, right?

204
00:18:43,924 --> 00:18:46,782
We haven't broken up.

205
00:18:46,782 --> 00:18:51,782
Because... things aren't going well with my wife➡

206
00:18:51,782 --> 00:18:53,815
They've decided to get divorced.

207
00:18:53,815 --> 00:18:58,155
Do you believe that? That's a common phrase for unfaithful men.

208
00:18:58,155 --> 00:19:00,848
I understand.

209
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:03,188
I know, but...

210
00:19:07,419 --> 00:19:11,716
I always thought Chinami would become like this someday.

211
00:19:11,716 --> 00:19:16,386
Because of love, I can't see anything and can't think about anything➡

212
00:19:16,386 --> 00:19:19,584
Someday I will make myself and those around me unhappy.

213
00:19:21,023 --> 00:19:23,056
what? that.

214
00:19:25,122 --> 00:19:28,155
Chinami these days is weird.

215
00:19:28,155 --> 00:19:30,320
Neglect yourself➡

216
00:19:30,320 --> 00:19:34,353
It's like anyone can fill in the empty hole.

217
00:19:34,353 --> 00:19:36,386
It's painful to watch.

218
00:19:38,089 --> 00:19:42,551
It's painful for Ayyo too.

219
00:19:42,551 --> 00:19:45,287
What about me... Even though I like light.

220
00:19:47,155 --> 00:19:50,056
Even though I love light, I don't want to admit it➡

221
00:19:50,056 --> 00:19:52,419
You've been making fun of me for being in love, haven't you?

222
00:19:52,419 --> 00:19:55,254
different…. Even so, it's me too➡

223
00:19:55,254 --> 00:19:58,056
If it's convenient for you, go out with a guy.

224
00:19:58,056 --> 00:20:01,584
That's not true... Me and the light➡

225
00:20:01,584 --> 00:20:05,518
I'm dealing with love properly.

226
00:20:05,518 --> 00:20:07,551
Ayase is the only one running away.

227
00:20:11,485 --> 00:20:14,122
Chinami doesn't understand my feelings!

228
00:20:14,122 --> 00:20:16,386
Even Ayase doesn't understand my feelings!

229
00:20:28,683 --> 00:20:31,452
⚞Tat tat tut…(footsteps)

230
00:20:36,990 --> 00:20:41,957
Zaaa… (Rain sound)

231
00:20:54,056 --> 00:20:56,089
Bassat

232
00:21:06,254 --> 00:21:09,386
≪“As expected”➡

233
00:21:09,386 --> 00:21:14,254
I feel bad that my friend said that≫

234
00:21:14,254 --> 00:21:21,924
♬〜

235
00:21:21,924 --> 00:21:23,957
Hey, hey, cutie, where are you going?

236
00:21:23,957 --> 00:21:25,990
Just get a refill of your drink.

237
00:21:28,287 --> 00:21:31,188
Another highball. (Clerk) Is it okay to use the same whiskey?

238
00:21:31,188 --> 00:21:33,221
Yeah. (Clerk) Yes.

239
00:21:33,221 --> 00:21:41,320
♬〜

240
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:43,353
Why don't we both drink?

241
00:21:43,353 --> 00:21:51,749
♬〜

242
00:21:51,749 --> 00:21:54,287
(Murata) Sorry for the inconvenience. ➡

243
00:21:54,287 --> 00:21:56,320
It's totally okay now.

244
00:21:56,320 --> 00:22:01,990
♬〜

245
00:22:01,990 --> 00:22:04,023
sorry….

246
00:22:06,957 --> 00:22:09,023
I don't want to try it anymore.

247
00:22:11,287 --> 00:22:13,320
Huh?

248
00:22:15,419 --> 00:22:17,782
I think it's wrong.

249
00:22:19,617 --> 00:22:23,881
Using Murata for your own feelings.

250
00:22:23,881 --> 00:22:26,155
That's normal. It's okay.

251
00:22:26,155 --> 00:22:31,749
Not good. If I keep going like this➡

252
00:22:31,749 --> 00:22:35,155
I hate myself even more.

253
00:22:39,881 --> 00:22:43,924
So... I'm sorry.

254
00:23:01,188 --> 00:23:03,221
Murata...

255
00:23:07,452 --> 00:23:09,485
Thank you so far.

256
00:23:12,881 --> 00:23:15,749
it was fun.

257
00:23:15,749 --> 00:23:26,815
♬〜

258
00:23:26,815 --> 00:23:29,419
Bright.

259
00:23:29,419 --> 00:23:33,617
(Male) Morning... no, around noon.

260
00:23:33,617 --> 00:23:35,650
Is it nearby? house.

261
00:23:35,650 --> 00:23:37,683
